31/07/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Security forces reportedly are conducting exercises aimed at assessing the readiness to react and respond to a terror threat in the wake of recent bombings in London and Egypt, according to sources cited in Saturday's (30 July) edition of Kathimerini. Sources say the readiness of emergency services is also being examined. Scenarios involving a variety of possible terrorist attacks on Greece reportedly are being explored, so that any problems that surface can be fixed as soon as possible. (Kathimerini - 30/07/05)
